description.plain: The fourth track off Erin Rae’s 2018 album Putting On Airs, Bad Mind sees her looking back on her childhood growing up in the South in the 1990s. Described as a “thematic centerpiece of the record” by NPR, Bad Mind discusses Erin Rae’s experiences with internalized homophobia.

body.plain: The fourth track off Erin Rae’s 2018 album Putting On Airs, Bad Mind sees her looking back on her childhood growing up in the South in the 1990s. Described as a “thematic centerpiece of the record” by NPR, Bad Mind discusses Erin Rae’s experiences with internalized homophobia.

annotations:
I don’t wanna have a bad mind
 I don’t wanna have a bad mind
 I don’t wanna have a bad mind

This line has two interplaying interpretations. One is her saying that she does not want to acknowledge that she loves women. The other, further into the song, is her saying that she does not want to hurt others by hiding herself: “I never had the courage to tell you until now.”
